'''''Coenophlebia''''' is a genus of [[neotropical]] charaxine [[butterfly|butterflies]] in the family [[Nymphalidae]], native to [[Colombia]], [[Peru]], [[Brazil]], [[Bolivia]] and [[Ecuador]]. It is a [[monotypic]] genus. The single species is  '''''Coenophlebia archidona'''''. The habitat consists of rainforests and transitional cloudforests at altitudes between 100 and 800 meters.

The [[wingspan]] is about 90 mm.<ref>[http://www.sangay.eu/ficha-principale.php?lang=en&ref=351 Parque Nacional Sangay]</ref> Adults mimic fallen leaves. They are attracted to decaying matter.<ref>[http://www.learnaboutbutterflies.com/Amazon%20-%20Coenophlebia%20archidona.htm Butterflies of the Amazon and Andes]</ref>

